---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Guitar Tab Reader" description="Privacy policy for the Guitar Tab Reader app.">
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: June 22, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Overview</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Guitar Tab Reader ("we", "our", or "the app") is a free tool for reading and playing Guitar Pro files. We built it with privacy as the default: the app does not require an account, and we do not collect, store, or transmit your personal data.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-2"><strong>None.</strong> We do not collect any personal information. There are no accounts to create, no sign-in, and no profiles.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Your Files</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">The tab and Guitar Pro files you open stay on your own device. They are never uploaded to us or to any third party. We have no access to your files, and the app works fully offline.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">No Tracking or Analytics</h2>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>We do not use analytics or tracking SDKs.</li>
          <li>We do not show ads or use advertising identifiers.</li>
          <li>We do not profile your behavior or sell or share any data.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">App Preferences</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Settings such as zoom level, selected track, and theme are saved locally on your device so the app remembers your preferences. This information never leaves your device.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">We do not integrate any third-party analytics, advertising, or backend services. If the app is distributed through an app store (such as Apple's App Store), that store may collect its own usage and download statistics under its own privacy policy, which we do not control.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">Because we do not collect any personal information, Guitar Tab Reader is safe for users of all ages. We do not knowingly collect data from anyone, including children.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@guitartabreader.app" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">support@guitartabreader.app</a>.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
